<h2 id="timestamp">Timestamp</h2>

<p>A point in time, usually with millisecond precision, represented as an
<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601" class="external">ISO 8601</a> date string (eg â€œ2021-06-11T02:51:11.000Zâ€). Timestamps
are in the UTC timezone as denoted by the â€œZâ€ suffix.</p>

<h2 id="bignumber">BigNumber</h2>

<p>A number, represented as a String, which can have arbitrary size or precision.
Most Centrapay APIs that deal with transactable value (ie. assets, payments,
etc) represent the value as BigNumbers. Depending on the context, a BigNumber
may be used to represent an integer or a decimal amount.</p>

<h2 id="monetary">Monetary</h2>

<p>A monetary amount in a currency, represented as an Object. The amount is
usually an integer in the smallest denomination for the currency (ie cents) but
may be a decimal value for some currencies (eg Bitcoin). The currency is
typically represented as an <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217" class="external">ISO 4217</a> code.</p>

